alerts.title: Wind Advisory
alerts.description: ...HIGH WINDS LIKELY TODAY IN THE HIGHER ELEVATIONS OF THE NORTH CAROLINA MOUNTAINS... ...GUSTY WINDS ACROSS THE LOWER ELEVATIONS... .Gusty southerly to southwesterly winds around a strong surface low associated with large upper storm system will affect the region through early this evening. Gusty northwest winds are possible across high elevations focused across the northern mountains late tonight into Monday morning. ...WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 PM EDT THIS EVENING... The National Weather Service in Greenville-Spartanburg has issued a Wind Advisory, which is in effect until 10 PM EDT this evening. * LOCATIONS...The Piedmont and Foothills of the Carolinas and northeast Georgia. * HAZARDS...Strong wind gusts. * TIMING...Through 10 PM EDT this evening. * WINDS...South 15 to 25 mph with gusts up to 45 mph. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result.
